cienaCesDhcpv6ClientMIB.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientMIB

revisions.description: LDRA - updated cienaCesDhcpv6LdraMplsVcName to allow the VC name length up to 31 characters.
LDRA - updated Dhcpv6LdraVsName and Dhcpv6LdraMplsName to allow the VS name length up to 31 characters.
LDRA - added missing DHCP Relay global statistic.
LDRA - added support for Q-in-Q VS and MPLS VS relay agents.
LDRA - added new global statistics, ability to clear global stats.
Added length checks for LDRA IntId, rid values. EnterpriseID can be unsigned 32
Added support for Lightweight DHCPv6 Relay Agent (LDRA). The functionality is similar to that for the L2 relay agent.
The ReconfigureState was included by mistake. It should not be visible to the SNMP user until the feature is completed.
The OptionCodeIndex incorrectly began at 0. It was changed to begin at 1.
The notification cienaCesDhcpv6ClientOptionDisabledNotification, neither implemented nor released, was removed.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessState.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessState

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessAutoConfigState.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessAutoConfigState

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessPrefLifetime.description: The preferred lifetime in seconds of the current lease.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessValidLifetime.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessValidLifetime
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessValidLifetime.description: The valid lifetime in seconds of the current lease.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessLeaseExpire.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessLeaseExpire
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessLeaseExpire.description: The remaining seconds until the current lease expires.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessClientId.description: The full 'client ID' value associated with this lease.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessServerIpAddrType.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessServerIpAddrType
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessServerIpAddrType.description: The IP address type (IPv6) of the server from which this lease was obtained.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessServerIpAddr.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessServerIpAddr
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessServerIpAddr.description: The IP address of the server from which this lease was obtained.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessServerId.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessServerId
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessServerId.description: The full 'server ID' value associated with this lease.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessT1Time.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessT1Time
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessT1Time.description: The lease renewal (T1) time in seconds.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessT2Time.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessT2Time
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessT2Time.description: The lease rebind (T2) time in seconds.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsTable.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsTable
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the statistics for DHCPv6 per interface

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsEntry.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsEntry
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsTable.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsClear.description: This object clears the DHCPv6 session statistics.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsPktsRx.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsPktsRx
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsPktsRx.description: The number of DHCPv6 packets received by the client.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsReply.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsReply
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsReply.description: The number of DHCPv6 reply messages received by the client.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsAdvert.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsAdvert
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsAdvert.description: The number of DHCPv6 advertise messages received by the client.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRecfg.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRecfg
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRecfg.description: The number of DHCPv6 reconfigure messages received by the client.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsInvalid.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsInvalid
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsInvalid.description: The number of DHCPv6 invalid messages received by the client.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsPktsTx.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsPktsTx
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsPktsTx.description: The number of DHCPv6 messages sent by the client.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsSolicit.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsSolicit
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsSolicit.description: The number of DHCPv6 solicit messages sent by the client.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRequest.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRequest
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRequest.description: The number of DHCPv6 request messages sent by the client.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsConfirm.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsConfirm
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsConfirm.description: The number of DHCPv6 confirm messages sent by the client.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRenew.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRenew
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRenew.description: The number of DHCPv6 renew messages sent by the client.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRebind.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRebind
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRebind.description: The number of DHCPv6 rebind messages sent by the client.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsInfoReq.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsInfoReq
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsInfoReq.description: The number of DHCPv6 information request messages sent by the client.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRelease.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRelease
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsRelease.description: The number of DHCPv6 release messages sent by the client.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsDecline.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsDecline
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsDecline.description: The number of DHCPv6 decline messages sent by the client.

cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsTxFail.name: cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsTxFail
cienaCesDhcpv6ClientSessStatsTxFail.description: The number of DHCPv6 messages the client was unable to send.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraState.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraState
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraState.description: Specifies the global state of the Lightweight DHCPv6 Relay Agent.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraInterfaceId.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraInterfaceId
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraInterfaceId.description: Specifies the type of data to use in the InterfaceID option of LDRA messages.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRemoteId.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRemoteId
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRemoteId.description: Specifies the type of data to use in the RemoteID option of LDRA messages.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRemoteIdOption.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRemoteIdOption
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRemoteIdOption.description: If on, the RemoteID option will be added to client messages being relayed by LDRA.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRemoteIdEnterpriseNo.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRemoteIdEnterpriseNo
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRemoteIdEnterpriseNo.description: If the RemoteID option is on, this value will be used as the Enterprise Number in the RemoteID option field. Uses Broadband Forum value 3561 as default

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraForward.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraForward
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraForward.description: This object specifies the number of DHCPv6 packets forwarded rather than relayed. These are valid DHCPv6 frames that don't have a defined relay.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRelayed.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRelayed
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRelayed.description: This object specifies the number of DHCPv6 packets processed by the LDRA and not dropped.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraDropped.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraDropped
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraDropped.description: This object specifies the number of DHCPv6 packets processed by the LDRA and dropped. Inspect the detailed statistics on each relay for more details related to dropped packets.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraGlobalStatsClear.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraGlobalStatsClear
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraGlobalStatsClear.description: This object when set to 'clear(1)', clears the global DHCPv6 LDRA stats.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraNotForRelay.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraNotForRelay
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraNotForRelay.description: This object specifies the number of DHCPv6 packets passed to the relay, but were determined to not belong to the relay. The packets are dropped.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStateTable.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStateTable
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStateTable.description: Table allows changing configuration of DHCPv6 LDRA functionality for each cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVlan.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStateEntry.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStateEntry
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStateEntry.description: Entry in the table to configure DHCPv6 LDRA functionality.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVlan.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVlan
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVlan.description: This object specifies the VLAN on which DHCPv6 LDRA is configured.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraAdminState.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraAdminState
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraAdminState.description: This object allows the user to disable or enable DHCPv6 LDRA functionality on the given VLAN specified by cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVlan.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraOperState.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraOperState
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraOperState.description: This object shows the operational status of the DHCPv6 LDRA on given VLAN.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRowStatus.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRowStatus
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRowStatus.description: Set this object to 'Destroy' to terminate DHCPv6 LDRA Relaying on the VLAN specified by cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVlan. Set this object to 'CreateAndGo' to enable DHCPv6 LDRA Relaying on the VLAN specified by cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVlan.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraTrustTable.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraTrustTable
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraTrustTable.description: This table is used to specify the slot / ports and VLANs that the DHCPv6 LDRA can trust. This table has been deprecated in favor of the cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExtTrustTable which adds a column for port status.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraTrustEntry.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraTrustEntry
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraTrustEntry.description: Each entry in this table is used to specify the slot / port and VLAN to be trusted.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraPort.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraPort
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraPort.description: This object is used as an index in the table and is used to specify the port.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraTrustMode.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraTrustMode
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraTrustMode.description: This object is used to set the port as client trusted, server trusted or not trusted. Note that the client(1) mode is deprecated. That value will never be returned. Setting that value will set the mode to clientTrust(2) instead.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStatsTable.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStatsTable
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStatsTable.description: Table to display L2 statistics for each cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVlan.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStatsEntry.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStatsEntry
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStatsEntry.description: Entry in the table to display LDRA stats.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraPktsForRelay.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraPktsForRelay
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraPktsForRelay.description: This object specifies the number of packets sent to this relay process.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRelayedClient.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRelayedClient
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRelayedClient.description: This object specifies the number of client sourced DHCPv6 packets relayed.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRelayedServer.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRelayedServer
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRelayedServer.description: This object specifies the number of server sourced DHCPv6 packets relayed.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraUntrustedClientPortPkt.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraUntrustedClientPortPktsRx
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraUntrustedClientPortPkt.description: This object specifies the number of client DHCPv6 packets dropped because they were received on untrusted client ports.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraUntrustedServerPortPkt.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraUntrustedServerPortPktsRx
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraUntrustedServerPortPkt.description: This object specifies the number of server DHCPv6 packets dropped because they were received on untrusted server ports.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraFailedValidationPktDro.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraFailedValidationPktDrop
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraFailedValidationPktDro.description: This object specifies the number of DHCPv6 packets dropped due to failed validation.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraInvalidConfigPktDrop.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraInvalidConfigPktDrop
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraInvalidConfigPktDrop.description: This object specifies the number of DHCPv6 packets dropped due to LDRA configuration issues.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExceededHopCountPktDro.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExceededHopCountPktDrop
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExceededHopCountPktDro.description: This object specifies the number of DHCPv6 packets dropped due to hop count in the packet exceeding hop count the limit.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExceedMTUPktDrop.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExceedMTUPktDrop
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExceedMTUPktDrop.description: This object specifies the number of DHCPv6 packets dropped because the new relay frame size would exceed the MTU.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraNoTrustedServerPktDrop.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraNoTrustedServerPktDrop
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraNoTrustedServerPktDrop.description: This object specifies the number of DHCPv6 packets dropped because there are no server trusted ports configured.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraNoTrustedClientPktDrop.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraNoTrustedClientPktDrop
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraNoTrustedClientPktDrop.description: This object specifies the number of DHCPv6 packets dropped because there are no client trusted ports configured.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIPv6FragBadExtHdrPktDr.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIPv6FragBadExtHdrPktDrop
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIPv6FragBadExtHdrPktDr.description: This object specifies the number of DHCPv6 packets dropped due to IPv6 packet extension headers that could not be processed.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraGeneralErrors.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraGeneralErrors
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraGeneralErrors.description: This object specifies the number of DHCPv6 packets dropped due to unclassified errors.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStatsClear.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStatsClear
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraStatsClear.description: This object when set to 'true', clears DHCPv6 LDRA stats for given VLAN.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidStringTable.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidStringTable
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidStringTable.description: This table is used to specify CID strings for slot / ports and VLANs that the DHCP relay agent can specify in Option 82 CID information.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidStringEntry.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidStringEntry
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidStringEntry.description: Each entry in this table is used to specify an interface id string for slot / port and VLAN combinations.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidStringPort.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidStringPort
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidStringPort.description: This object is used as an index in the table and is used to specify the port.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidString.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidString
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidString.description: This object is used to get and set the IntID string for the port.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidStringRowStatus.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidStringRowStatus
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraIntidStringRowStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table set this object to 'createAndGo'. To delete a row in this table set this object to 'destroy'.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidStringTable.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidStringTable
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidStringTable.description: This table is used to specify RID strings for slot / ports and VLANs that the DHCP relay agent can specify in Option 82 RID information.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidStringEntry.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidStringEntry
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidStringEntry.description: Each entry in this table is used to specify an RID string for slot / port and VLAN combinations.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidStringPort.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidStringPort
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidStringPort.description: This MIB object is used as an index in the table and is used to specify the port.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidString.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidString
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidString.description: This MIB object is used to get and set the RID string for the port.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidStringRowStatus.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidStringRowStatus
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraRidStringRowStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table set this object to 'createAndGo'. To delete a row in this table set this object to 'destroy'.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExtTrustTable.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExtTrustTable
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExtTrustTable.description: This table is used to specify the ports and VLANs that the DHCPv6 LDRA can trust. This table is the same as cienaCesDhcpv6LdraTrustTable with the addition of a column for the port status.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExtTrustEntry.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExtTrustEntry
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExtTrustEntry.description: Each entry in this table is used to specify the port and VLAN to be trusted.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExtPortState.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExtPortState
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExtPortState.description: This object reports whether the specified port is active or inactive.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExtTrustMode.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExtTrustMode
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraExtTrustMode.description: This object is used to set the port as client trusted, server trusted or not trusted. Note that the client(1) mode is deprecated. That value will never be returned. Setting that value will set the mode to clientTrust(2) instead.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsStateTable.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsStateTable
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsStateTable.description: Table allows changing configuration of DHCPv6 LDRA functionality for each VS.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsStateEntry.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsStateEntry
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsStateEntry.description: Entry in the table to configure DHCPv6 LDRA functionality.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsVlan.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsVlan
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsVlan.description: This object specifies the VS VLAN on which the DHCPv6 LDRA is configured.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsName.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsName
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsName.description: This object shows the name of the VS VLAN on which the DHCPv6 LDRA is configured.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsAdminState.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsAdminState
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsAdminState.description: This object allows the user to disable or enable DHCPv6 LDRA functionality on the given VS VLAN specified by cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsVlan.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsOperState.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsOperState
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsOperState.description: This object shows the operational status of the DHCPv6 LDRA on the given VS VLAN.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsRowStatus.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsRowStatus
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsRowStatus.description: Set this object to 'Destroy' to terminate DHCPv6 LDRA Relaying on the VS VLAN specified by cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsVlan. Set this object to 'CreateAndGo' to enable DHCPv6 LDRA Relaying on the VS VLAN specified by cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsVlan.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsTrustTable.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsTrustTable
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsTrustTable.description: This table is used to specify the VLANs, ports and sub-VLANs that the DHCPv6 LDRA can trust.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsTrustEntry.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsTrustEntry
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsTrustEntry.description: Each entry in this table is used to specify the VLAN, port and sub-VLAN to be trusted.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsPort.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsPort
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsPort.description: This object is used as an index in the table and is used to specify the VS port.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsSubVlan.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsSubVlan
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsSubVlan.description: This object specifies the sub-VLAN on which the DHCPv6 LDRA is configured. Note that the special value 0 means that no sub-VLAN is associated with this particular trust entry.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsPortState.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsPortState
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsPortState.description: This object reports whether the specified port and sub-VLAN is active or inactive.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsTrustMode.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsTrustMode
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsTrustMode.description: This object is used to set the port and sub-VLAN as client trusted, server trusted or not trusted. Note that the client(1) mode is deprecated. That value will never be returned. Setting that value will set the mode to clientTrust(2) instead.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsStatsTable.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsStatsTable
cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsStatsTable.description: Table to display VS statistics for each VS LDRA.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsPktsForRelay.description: This object specifies the number of packets sent to this relay process.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsRelayedClient.description: This object specifies the number of client sourced DHCPv6 packets relayed.

cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsGeneralErrors.name: cienaCesDhcpv6LdraVsGeneralErrors
